    ## 3. Now after looking at the qc data we can trim the adaptors using the fast p command in a slrum. I used the following for my slurm script. 
fastp \
    -i 22018FL-04-01-12_S12_L002_R1_001.fastq.gz \
    -I 22018FL-04-01-12_S12_L002_R2_001.fastq.gz \
    -o L002_R1_001.trimmed.fastq.gz \
    -O L002_R2_001.trimmed.fastq.gz \
    --qualified_quality_phred 30 \
    --unqualified_percent_limit 0 \
    --detect_adapter_for_pe \ 
    --thread 8

